Former rugby player Ben Cohen and his wife Abby have separated after 11 years of marriage.

The athlete and activist, who was part of England's 2003 World Cup winning squad, announced on Wednesday the couple were taking time time apart.

In a joint statement, their representative said: 'Ben and Abby Cohen have agreed to take time apart to deal with some marital issues but remain fully committed to the welfare of their children.

